[...]
I got under the van and the first thing I checked was the WR1 relay...
sure enough the 15 amp fuse was fried. replaced the fuse, but still no
start.
Taking a page from Muir, with the key out of the ignition van in neutral
handbrake on, I took a screwdriver and bridged the two large bolts on
the solinoid. There was a spark, so I was clearly getting current... but
the starter did not engage.
Time for a new Starter?
Thanks,
Chris
